cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a novel feature fusion module, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also mention the use of multibox detectors, which are a type of neural network architecture (cs.NE). Finally, the paper reports results on the Pascal VOC and COCO datasets, which are commonly used benchmarks in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
